Pre-requisite:
1.  Install VS Code which will be our editor
2.  Android phone
3.  Install Android studio and Android SDK
4.  Install Google USB Driver

Then use the following link to install flutter:
  https://flutter.io/docs/get-started/install/windows

To run app on the device:

1. First conect device tolaptop
2. switch on USB debugging mode as per following link:
      https://developer.android.com/studio/debug/dev-options
3. Run "flutter devices" to check if device is showing
4. Run "flutter run" to run the app
5. press "r" to hot reload (refresh app without compiling again)
